  "texts": [
    "E. Throughput SurfacePer-node throughput is:T node (V) = κ • min(c, r, b, s).Cluster throughput accounts for diminishing returns:T (H, V) = H • T node (V) • ϕ(H),where:ϕ(H) = 1 1 + ω log H,reflects increased coordination overhead and replication costs.",
    "F. Coordination Overhead SurfaceWrite-heavy workloads impose additional overhead.",
    "Let λ w be the write arrival rate.K(H, V) = ρ • L coord (H) • λ w T (H, V).This captures the intuition that coordination overhead:• increases with write load,• decreases when throughput increases,• rises with larger cluster size.",
    "G. Monetary Cost SurfaceIf C node (V) is the cloud cost for an instance with resources V, total cost is:C(H, V) = H • C node (V).",
    "H. Multi-Objective OptimizationWe define the objective:F (H, V) = αL(H, V) + βC(H, V) + γK(H, V), subject to: L(H, V) ≤ L max, T (H, V) ≥ T min.This creates a two-dimensional non-convex optimization problem."
